<concept id="adoption-tools-overview">

<title>Adoption Tools Overview</title>

  <p>
  This toolkit supports both foster teams and potential adopters by providing clear, modular resources that make it easier to understand and care for Cerberus. 
  Each tool is designed to be practical, shareable, and focused on setting him up for long-term success.
  </p>

  <p>
    <ul>
    What’s Included:
      <li>Housing & Compatibility Checklist: Screen for fit without sifting through long bios</li>
      <li>Printable Fact Sheet: A 1-page overview for meetings, home visits, or quick reviews</li>
      <li>Health & Medical Record: Editable and shareable snapshot of Cerberus’s care history</li>
      <li>Daily Routine Guide: AM-to-PM structure to reduce guesswork and support transition</li>
      <li>Training & Behavior Log: Track and document progress over time</li>
      <li>Photo Repository: Captioned, high-resolution images ready for listings and social media</li>
      <li>External Breed Reference: Context for breed mix (Boxer–German Shepherd)</li>
      <li>Contact Sheet: Centralized info for coordinating across team members</li>
      <li>Frozen Treat Recipe & Enrichment Tools: Support for mental stimulation in foster homes</li>
    </ul>
  </p>
